## E.22 A closing observation

The reader is where source becomes data. Understanding it opens up meta-programming, source-transformation, and IDE integration in ways that treating source as opaque strings would foreclose.

Motoi's reader is exposed as a verb. You can call it, inspect its output, feed it back into the pipeline. That transparency is what makes reader-time introspection viable.

